  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Envelope 1: CCCM, Protection, S-NFI and WASH Response to Support People Affected by Food Insecurity in IPC 4 and 5 Areas in South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall humanitarian situation in South Sudan in 2021 remains a concern with an estimated 8.3 million people to be in need of assistance, according to the 2021 Humanitarian Needs Overview. Through this project, IOM will contribute to reducing and mitigating protection threats for persons living in IPC 4 and 5 locations who are facing the highest levels of food insecurity and malnutrition, through the provision of multi-sector lifesaving humanitarian assistance in a safe, dignified, accessible and participatory manner. As such, IOM aims to meet the multi-faceted needs of displaced, returnee and host populations in said locations through the provision of life saving and life-sustaining services including shelter and non-food items, camp coordination and camp management, water, sanitation and hygiene, primary health care as well as enhancing the psychosocial well-being of affected populations through integrated protection, gender-based violence, and mental health and psychosocial support programming.</narrative>
  </description>
